The Vice President visited the McAllen Border Patrol Station in Texas and spoke about the immigration crisis at the southern border. He emphasized the need for Congress to take action and praised the efforts of Customs and Border Protection personnel. He also mentioned the reduction in the number of illegal immigrants crossing the border, which he attributed to the efforts of Mexico. The Vice President expressed concern about the overcrowding and called for changes in the law to prevent human traffickers from exploiting vulnerable families. He defended the care being provided to detainees but acknowledged the challenges faced by the system. He criticized Democrats for their response to the crisis and called for bipartisan solutions. The Vice President also mentioned the need for border security and the construction of a wall. He emphasized the importance of reforming asylum laws to address the crisis.